article.headline: N.J. Tech 56, Wagner 51
article.story: NEWARK, N.J. -- Isaiah Wilkerson scored 17 points and grabbed 13 rebounds to help New Jersey Tech hold off Wagner 56-51 on Tuesday night. Wilkerson was 4-for-13 from the field and 0-for-4 from 3-point range as neither team shot well. The Highlanders (2-2) were 18-for-56 from the field (32.1 percent) while the Seahawks (0-3) were 19-for-62 (30.6 percent). Wagner shot 3-for-22 from beyond the arc. The Seahawks led 20-16 with 3:49 left in the first half, then the Highlanders used an 8-0 run to lead 24-20 at the break. Wagner regained the lead at 32-31 on Michael Orock's three-point play with 15:27 left. The teams stayed within two points of each other until Wilkerson's dunk with 4:51 left put the Highlanders on top 49-45. New Jersey Tech extended the lead to seven with 1:36 left and Wagner could get no closer than four. Orock had career highs of 22 points and 14 rebounds.
